title: Grateful Dead Live at Cal Expo on 1994-06-10
lineage: Neumann KM140's > DAT > CDR > EAC > CD Wave > mkwACT > SHN v3
description: Here Comes Sunshine, The Same Thing, Lazy River Road, El Paso*, Loser, Easy Answers-> Don't Ease Me In Sugar Magnolia-> Touch Of Gray-> Looks Like Rain, Way to Go Home -> Drums-> Space>, The Other One-> Wharf Rat-> Around & Around-> Sunshine Daydream, E: Brokedown Palace

reviews.review_text: good stuff nice sound for audience version-clean sound nice show  thanks again to all involved in the internet archive ofor all the contributions and hard work to make these gems available to all

Good recording and show Kudos to the taper of this recording. Very nice to hear these audience tapes that sound as good as or better than the boards.

Excellent version of Wharf Rat.

Cal Expo was a warm welcome to CA As I listen to this show, I remember the Cal Expo Show I was at a couple years earlier.  They opened with a sarchastic COLD RAIN.  It was 95* for that, my first CA show.  I saw many more.  I can see Jerry up on the wide open stage, just jammin' away.  I'm from Wisconsin.  Cal Expo reminded me of a local county fair grounds where stock cars race.  I had a blast!  The sound was great as is this.
                            JP in Madison

good memories even though i wasn;t actually at this show. I do have a very fond memory of listening to it while tripping balls driving to my hotel room with my freinds after an other ones show at star lake in PA. The drumz/space is absolutely bone chilling and I vividly remember everyone in the car just being completely silent while it's playing, half because of the liquid acid we had taken and half because we couldn;t say anything cause we were to scared because of the space.

Why I love AUDS! :-D Any post Hornsby SBD quite literally makes me nauseous - it's like listening while you have a cold.  AUDs like this one are essential to reminding us that, yes, there actually was an audience in attendance at Grateful Dead shows after Bruce left, and yes, the band could still kick ass and bring it to town on occasion.  Thank you so much for this, Chris!
Genuine Excellent recording excellent playing. Jerry really nails the end of LOOKS LIKE RAIN.
Crystal clear recording, but of a bit of a lame show. First set is good, second set disjointed & listless.

First Set Lame / Second Set Better They closed with "Don't Ease" for the 2nd time in 3 nights and it definitely felt like they were just mailing it in.  That said, I thought the 2nd set was super fun.  This was my only split Sugar Mag, which was a treat. Don't know if it comes through on this recording but Phil was thunderous on The Other One coming out of space.
HAD TO BE THERE Bob wanted to do Victim out of space so bad and there was a few minutes of musical back and forth until Phil stomped his foot and dropped the bomb. SUBLIME!

I am on an amazing journey I am listening to every 1994 show in order, mining for gold. 

Jerry puts the Here Comes Sunshine lyrics up against a wall and executes them! 

Set 1 Highlights : Lazy River Road, Loser (WOW). At the end of Don't Ease Me In, a taper calls this Cal Expo run as "possibly the last one."

Set 2 Highlights: Brokedown Palace? Second set is pretty bad. Some parts of the Wharf Rat solo are cool.

Well, the night before this one is definitely the winner. On to Seattle for the next run. See you at the show.
